Solhekol (Sky Sports): &ldquo;Progress is being made in talks between Chelsea and Zenit on Leandro Paredes. He&rsquo;s a very good passer of the ball, very solid. He&rsquo;s also good at set-pieces. He is the player that Maurizio Sarri wants. I think he&rsquo;s the most likely replacement for Fabregas&ldquo;<br />
<br />
Solhekol: &ldquo;Zenit spent about &pound;25m on him just 18 months ago and they want more than that - they&rsquo;re asking for about &pound;35m. But if Chelsea and Zenit can come to a compromise on the money, I think wages won&rsquo;t be a problem for Chelsea. We&rsquo;re told progress is being made.&rdquo;

@ChelseaFC<br />
Ruben Loftus-Cheek, with a back problem, is the only player unavailable. <br />
